12050@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The deer are not a part of the original wild deer flock in Scandinavia, but are descendants from tame reindeer from the 1800's Otherwise you will find rabbit, red fox, arctic fox, lynx and various smaller animals (mouses, weasels, lemmings) as well as different kinds of birds (including everything from small sparrows via seagulls and ravens to eagles).@1@58@@oe@20-11-2007
12060@unknown@formal@none@1@S@Many places you will find herds of sheep.@1@8@@oe@20-11-2007
12080@unknown@formal@none@1@S@Legal status@1@2@@oe@20-11-2007
12110@unknown@formal@none@1@S@It was therefore not an easy task when Minister of Environment Gro Harlem Brundtland wanted to declare the area a national park in the late 1970s This was the first national park in Norway where a major portion (50% was private property.@1@42@@oe@20-11-2007
